FORT FORELHOST: THE LAST REDOUBT
Standalone Dungeon Module — The Rift Mountains Party Tier: Expert (AP 10) | Estimated Runtime: 2-3 hours Primary PC: Alfonso | All PCs engaged

DUNGEON DASHBOARD
Function: The party breaches an ancient Dragon Priest tomb that has been repurposed as a sterile bioweapons laboratory. Antoine of Forelhost is not here — he and Rahgot are elsewhere reverse-engineering Alfonso's plague. But his work is readable in the walls, his methodology is visible in every modification, and his research notes are the primary reward. The dungeon introduces Antoine as Alfonso's intellectual rival and foil — a clinical, sterile scientist who treats plague as engineering where Alfonso treats it as divine art. Alfonso meets his enemy through his science before he ever meets him in person.
The Gimmick — Death as Containment: The mass suicide of Forelhost's congregation four thousand years ago saturated the tomb with concentrated death energy. Antoine exploited this — the death ward acts as a natural sterile barrier, killing all foreign biological agents that enter. His laboratory exists inside this death-sterile zone. The puzzle is: how do you enter a biolab whose containment system is powered by four thousand years of accumulated death?
The Infection: The climax is a containment puzzle with multiple solutions. The party's approach determines how much pathogen exposure they receive. This is NOT optional — the party WILL be exposed to some degree. The question is severity.
Who can be infected:
Alfonso: IMMUNE. He is a Peryite Lich. Pathogens are his medium. He reads the plague like a musician reads sheet music.
Saijah: TEMPORARY. Hircine's predator gift is purging foreign agents from her blood. Within 48 hours, the infection burns out. She feels feverish for a day, then fine.
Davinia: VULNERABLE. The pathogen feeds on Restoration magic. The Crown's magical presence makes her a prime host.
Orion: VULNERABLE. Vampire biology is complex — the pathogen interacts unpredictably with his undead metabolism. Slower progression but harder to cure.
Ylva: RESISTANT. Werewolf metabolism fights infection aggressively. She'll be sick but won't die.
NPCs (Bjorn, Nora, Varon): Stay outside with the cart. They do not enter the tomb.
Reward Tier (Expert): 2000-2500 gold equivalent per player in alchemical reagents, research value, and intelligence. 2-3 Rare items from Antoine's lab.
Danger Level (Short Rest): TN 7 (Exposed) in the outer tomb. TN 3 (Suicidal) inside the laboratory — the pathogen is in the air.

