SECTION 2: THE OSSUARY
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
Function: The party enters the mass suicide chamber and confronts the scale of what happened here. Environmental storytelling delivers the horror. Alfonso reads the death-energy as a containment mechanism. This is the puzzle setup — understanding the death ward is the key to Section 4.
Location: The central chamber of Forelhost. A massive natural cavern enlarged by Nordic stonework. The ceiling is lost in darkness.
THE ROOM (Read Aloud)
"The corridor opens into a cathedral of death. The chamber is vast — a hundred feet across, the ceiling vanishing into shadow above. Tiers of stone shelving line the walls from floor to darkness, and on every shelf, in every alcove, piled in the corners and stacked along the floor, are bones. Skeletons. Thousands of them. Men, women, children — whole families curled together in their final moments, their postures preserved by the dry, cold air.
They are not scattered or disturbed. They are arranged. Each body was placed deliberately — hands folded, eyes closed, heads facing the center of the chamber. Whatever killed them, they went willingly. They laid down and they died.
At the center of the chamber stands a stone altar. On it, a massive iron cauldron — tarnished black, crusted with four-thousand-year-old residue. The air around it shimmers faintly, like heat haze. You can feel something radiating from this room — not warmth, not cold. Absence. The air feels thinner. Sounds are muffled. Your skin prickles. Magic feels harder to reach here, as if the room is drinking it.
On the far wall, past the altar, is a sealed stone door. Unlike the fortress gate, this one is closed. It has been modified — recently. Fresh mortar seals the edges. A brass mechanism has been bolted to the ancient stone, and beside it, etched into a copper plate in neat modern handwriting, is a warning in Common:
'CONTAINMENT THRESHOLD. DO NOT BREACH WITHOUT PROTOCOL. THE WARD IS THE SEAL.'"
Then improvise from: The silence is total — not quiet, but dead. Sound doesn't echo; it's absorbed. The sweet chemical smell is stronger here. The bone-dust on the floor is undisturbed except for a single path of footprints leading from the entrance to the sealed door and back again — someone has been walking this route regularly.
WHAT'S IN THIS ROOM
The arranged skeletons: What they see: Thousands of skeletons arranged deliberately. If they investigate (Magic TN 12): These people were poisoned. The residue in the cauldron matches — a massive batch of toxic compound, distributed to the congregation. They drank it willingly. The arrangement confirms ritual — this was a religious act, not a massacre. They believed death was preferable to a world without dragons. Why planted here: The emotional and historical weight of Forelhost. This is not a dungeon. It is a grave.
The iron cauldron and the shimmer: What they see: An ancient cauldron radiating something that dampens magic. If they investigate (Magic TN 14): The cauldron is the nexus of the death ward. Four thousand years of concentrated death-energy — the combined spiritual residue of thousands of simultaneous deaths — has created a permanent anti-biological field. Nothing living grows here. Nothing foreign survives. Bacteria, mold, parasites, pathogens — all die within minutes of entering this field. It is the most sterile environment in Skyrim. Antoine recognized this and built his laboratory inside it. Why planted here: THIS IS THE PUZZLE. The death ward is both the dungeon's defense and the laboratory's containment system. Understanding it is the key to Section 4.
ALFONSO'S SPECIAL READ (no roll — this is his domain): Alfonso doesn't need a check. He is a Peryite Lich. He reads death-energy the way a sailor reads wind. "The ward is elegant. Brutal, but elegant. Thousands of deaths, concentrated in a single ritual moment, created a permanent sterilization field. Anything biological that enters this space is systematically destroyed at the cellular level. Your prodigy — this Antoine — recognized what he had. He didn't build a laboratory. He found one that nature and fanaticism had already constructed. He just added a door."
The sealed stone door with modern modifications: What they see: An ancient door with fresh mortar and a brass mechanism. A warning sign. If they investigate: The mechanism is a pressure lock — it requires a specific sequence to open without disrupting the death ward that seals the laboratory. The warning sign is in Antoine's handwriting. He is meticulous, clinical, and arrogant enough to label his own security system in Common. Why planted here: The entrance to Section 3 and the setup for the Section 4 puzzle.
The footprints: What they see: A single path worn through the bone-dust. If they investigate: The footprints of one person, wearing boots, lead from the entrance to the sealed door and back out of the sanctum — but the most recent set goes only ONE way: out. Someone has been coming and going regularly, but their last trip was a departure. He left, and has not come back. The footprints are days old. Why planted here: Confirms Antoine's absence and recent departure.
THE MOVES
ALFONSO → READING THE DEATH WARD
What he wants: To understand the containment system. What's required: Being Alfonso. No roll.
Alfonso examines the ward └─→ He receives the full analysis above. He understands:
The ward kills all foreign biological agents
Antoine used it as a natural clean room
The brass mechanism controls access WITHOUT disrupting the ward
If the ward is disrupted (by forcing the door, destroying the mechanism, or overloading it with magic), the containment fails — and whatever is inside the lab enters the general atmosphere
The correct approach is to use the mechanism as designed
What Alfonso receives:
Category
Information
The Ward
Death-energy sterilization field. Kills all foreign biology.
The Mechanism
Pressure lock. Specific sequence opens the door safely.
The Risk
Forcing entry disrupts containment. Pathogen release.
Antoine's Method
He walks through using the mechanism. There IS a safe way in.

✓ ALFONSO'S WARD ANALYSIS COMPLETE. He knows the puzzle exists and what's at stake.
EXIT
The sealed door blocks progress. The mechanism must be solved (Section 4) or the door forced (with consequences). Likely next: Section 3 (if they explore the ossuary further) or Section 4 (the puzzle).

