SECTION 3: THE REFINERY
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
Function: Side chambers off the ossuary where Antoine has been processing raw materials. His methodology is visible — cold, precise, devoid of any divine element. Alfonso sees his rival's mind for the first time. Research notes provide intelligence and emotional fuel.
Location: Three alcoves branching from the ossuary, each repurposed by Antoine. Originally burial preparation chambers.
THE ROOM (Read Aloud)
"Three archways branch from the ossuary's east wall. Each has been modified — the ancient burial niches inside have been cleared of bones (stacked neatly against the walls, still respectful of the dead — this person is methodical even with skeletons) and replaced with workstations.
The first alcove contains a stone table covered in glass vessels — flasks, retorts, condensation tubes. An alchemist's distillation array, but cleaner than any you've seen. Every surface is scrubbed. Every instrument is precisely aligned. There is no dust.
The second alcove is a library. Shelves of books — some ancient, some modern. A desk with a reading lamp (enchanted, still glowing faintly). Open journals in a small, precise hand. Charcoal diagrams of cellular structures pinned to the walls.
The third alcove smells. Sweet, organic, wrong. The shelves hold sealed glass jars containing specimens — plant samples, tissue cultures, things suspended in amber fluid that you cannot identify. A locked cabinet stands against the far wall."
Then improvise from: The obsessive cleanliness. Every tool in its place. Labels on every jar in the same small handwriting. The contrast between the ancient tomb and the modern, clinical workspace is jarring — like finding a hospital inside a crypt.
WHAT'S IN THIS ROOM
Alcove 1 — The Distillery: What they see: Alchemical processing equipment. If they investigate (Magic TN 14): This is where Antoine processes the Tears of Rahgot — the extinct flower that grows only in Forelhost's blood-soaked soil. The distillation process extracts the floral toxin and concentrates it into a binding agent for his pathogen. The equipment is idle — he hasn't processed a batch recently. But the residue in the flasks confirms the Tears of Rahgot analysis Alfonso received from Peryite. Why planted here: Confirms Alfonso's Meadery findings. The evidence chain is now: pathogen → binding agent → Tears of Rahgot → this distillery → Antoine.
Alcove 2 — The Library / Research Notes: What they see: Books and journals. If they investigate: Antoine's research journals. See detailed breakdown below. Why planted here: The primary intelligence reward. Alfonso meets his rival's mind here.
Alcove 3 — The Specimen Room: What they see: Sealed jars with biological samples. A locked cabinet. If they investigate: The jars contain samples of Forelhost Strain 1.0 in various stages of development. The locked cabinet (Agility TN 16) contains three vials of refined Tears of Rahgot extract — the binding agent itself. These are worth a fortune to an alchemist or a bioweapons expert. Why planted here: Rare alchemical loot AND the reagent that proves Maven's Meadery was poisoned from this location (actionable intelligence for Maven's bounty).
ANTOINE'S RESEARCH JOURNALS
Three journals, each revealing a different facet of his character. Alfonso should read these. They are written in a precise, clinical hand with no emotion, no humor, and no self-doubt.
Journal 1: "Methodology"
"The congregation's mass death created ideal conditions. The death-energy sterilization field eliminates all competing biological agents within the containment zone. I have achieved a workspace purity that no surface laboratory could match. The irony is not lost on me — four thousand people killed themselves to serve their god, and their sacrifice now serves mine. Rahgot would approve. Efficiency through devotion."
"Strain 1.0 deployment in Riften produced acceptable results. Infection vector: contaminated mead vats. Transmission rate: 73% among consumers. Lethality without treatment: 89% within 14 days. Lethality WITH Restoration magic treatment: 94%. The anti-Restoration mechanism performed beyond projections. Healers accelerated the pathogen's reproduction cycle. Their cure was my delivery system."
"Data collected: incubation period, symptom progression, immune response curves, Restoration interaction coefficients. Sufficient for Strain 2.0 design parameters."
ALFONSO'S REACTION (GM direction): This is the professional insult. Antoine's methodology is flawless — mathematically perfect, clinically sterile, completely devoid of the divine. He treats plague like engineering. There is no Peryite, no Namira, no conversation with the gods of disease. He has built a machine that mimics pestilence without understanding what pestilence IS. To Alfonso, this is blasphemy. Not because the plague kills people — Alfonso's plagues kill people too. Because Antoine has stripped the godhood out of disease and left only a mechanism.
Journal 2: "Observations on the Priestess"
"The Kynareth-channeler who arrived in Riften performed an unexpected ritual. She offered her own life-force as a catalytic sacrifice to purify the most advanced case (Hemming Black-Briar). This was not standard Restoration magic. She used herself as the reagent. The cost to her was approximately 15 years of biological lifespan.
I did not anticipate self-sacrifice as a viable countermeasure. Strain 2.0 must account for this variable. If a healer is willing to burn years of life to cure a single patient, the pathogen must ensure such sacrifice is either insufficient or lethal to the healer. The cure must kill the curer."
What this tells the party: Antoine watched Danica cure the plague. He studied her technique. He is designing Strain 2.0 specifically to counter what she did. If the party ever needs Danica to cure this pathogen again, it might kill her.
Journal 3: "Regarding the Wardens"
"The mercenary company called the Obsidian Lanterns continues to disrupt regional operations. Their interference at Kynesgrove and the Pale cost us two operational assets. However, their plague-immune member is of greater interest than their combat capability.
I have just received field reports from Korvanjund. The data is... paradigm-shifting. The reports indicate the presence of a Peryite-aligned pathogen carrier among their ranks — a living bioweapons platform operating on divine frequency. Ulag the Breaker was infected during the engagement and has retreated to a secure fallback position to prevent structural failure. He is a compromised but invaluable asset.
I am departing Forelhost immediately to rendezvous with him. I will perform the extraction in the field and stabilize the sample for transport.
If the reports are accurate, this carrier represents a paradigm I have not considered: plague as communion rather than mechanism. If the divine frequency can be isolated and integrated into my sterile Strain 2.0 chassis, the result would be beyond anything I could achieve alone — a pathogen that is both engineered AND divine. The perfect plague."
What this tells the party:
Category
Information
Antoine knows about Alfonso
He has identified Alfonso as a Peryite bioweapons platform from field intel.
Ulag's status
Ulag is wounded and in hiding, NOT at Forelhost.
Antoine's location
Antoine is GONE. He has left this lab to go find Ulag.
The timeline
The clock on Strain 2.0 starts NOW. Antoine is actively acquiring the final component.
The stakes
If Antoine reaches Ulag and returns, he will create an uncurable super-plague.

EXIT
