━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
Function: The pathogen puzzle. The party must open the sealed door to the inner sanctum / laboratory without causing a catastrophic containment breach. This is the climax — the puzzle's outcome determines the severity of infection the party receives.
Location: The sealed stone door at the back of the ossuary. The brass mechanism is bolted to the ancient stone. The death ward shimmers visibly around the door frame.
THE PUZZLE: THE BRASS MECHANISM
The mechanism is a pressure-plate sequence built into the door frame. Five brass plates arranged vertically, each inscribed with a Dragon Cult alchemical symbol. They must be pressed in the correct order. The correct sequence reduces the death ward gradually, creating a narrow safe corridor through the containment field. The wrong sequence — or forcing the door — disrupts the ward entirely.
The Clues: The correct sequence is encoded in Antoine's Journal 1 (the methodology journal from Section 3). The relevant passage:
"Entry protocol: the ward is layered. Each layer corresponds to a phase of death. Shutdown sequence follows thanatological order: Cessation, Cooling, Rigidity, Decay, Dissolution. The living enter by reversing the process of dying."
The symbols on the brass plates are Dragon Cult alchemical notation. Translation requires either:
Magic TN 14 (general arcane knowledge)
Esbern's expertise (if they consulted him first — he can read Dragon Cult notation)
Alfonso's divine knowledge (automatic — Peryite speaks the language of death)
