GM NOTES
Alfonso is the star of this dungeon. Every room speaks to him specifically. The death ward, the sterile methodology, the journals, the Strain 2.0 folder — this is a conversation between two virologists conducted through their work. Give Alfonso's player space to react to what he finds. His disgust at Antoine's sterile, godless approach to plague is not just flavor — it's character definition. Alfonso creates plague as divine communion. Antoine creates plague as engineering. They are the same discipline pointed at different gods.
The infection is a narrative tool, not a punishment. The puzzle determines severity, but even the best outcome results in some exposure. This is intentional — the infection gives the party a personal, biological reason to chase Antoine. It also connects them to the Windhelm hook (where Alfonso's OTHER plague is eating the Stormcloak army) and creates demand for Danica's healing (if she rejoined the party).
The empty sarcophagus is the session's biggest reveal. The party has been fighting Dragon Cult operatives and draugr — foot soldiers. Forelhost is where they learn the generals are awake. Rahgot is not a historical figure. He is a living Dragon Priest walking the same roads they walk, with an alchemist-servant building weapons of ecological destruction. The sarcophagus carvings naming all five priests and the Konahrik apotheosis prophecy reframe the entire campaign — the Dragon Cult isn't just serving Alduin. The priests have their own endgame. Let the players sit with that.
The Tears of Rahgot are irreplaceable. If the party takes samples, Antoine loses access to his binding agent when he returns. If they destroy the flowers, Antoine's entire Forelhost operation is compromised. If they leave them, he continues production unimpeded. This is a strategic choice the party may not realize they're making.
Maven's bounty: The sealed culture samples + the Tears of Rahgot extract + Antoine's journals constitute overwhelming proof of the Meadery operation's origin. Delivering this to Maven earns the 5,000 gold AND deepens the alliance. Maven will want Antoine dead — which aligns with the party's interests for once.

